{{ "Source locators" | textToHeading('H1') }}

Source locators are needed so that the parser knows which files to parse, or to get data on a specific file after the primary parsing procedure

Source locators are set in the configuration, in method `ConfigurationInterface::classEntityFilterCondition()`_.
They can also be connected using plugins that implement interface `CustomSourceLocatorInterface`_

**Usage example:**

{{ 'public function getSourceLocators(): SourceLocatorsCollection
{
    return SourceLocatorsCollection::create(
        new RecursiveDirectoriesSourceLocator([
            "{$this->getProjectRoot()}/BumbleDocGen",
            "{$this->getProjectRoot()}/SelfDoc",
        ]),
    );
}' | textToCodeBlockRst('php') }}


All source locators must implement the `SourceLocatorInterface`_ interface.


